               <head>Mortgage; Higham; 1345</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111663">Higham</placeName>. 
                        <origDate when="1345">1345</origDate>.
                        Indenture, by which <persName>
                           <forename>Gilbert</forename> le <surname>Waleys</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111663">Higham (Heiham of the parish of Gaislee)</placeName></persName>, grants and impledges to <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>Richard</forename> of <surname>Gaislee</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111663">Higham (Heiham)</placeName>
                           </persName></persName>, and <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Fyche</surname>
                        </persName> of the same, for 100s., all lands and tenements held by him in the vill and fields of Heyham, from the date of this indenture, to the feast of St Margaret the Virgin next following, when he may recover possession by repaying the money. 
                        Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_111663">Higham (Heiham)</placeName>, on Palm Sunday, 19 Edw. III [20 March, 1345].
                     Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Passelewe</surname></persName>; <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname type="patronymic">son of Thomas</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname type="patronymic">son of Margaret</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> of <surname>Honedene</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Nichole</surname></persName>, and others. 
                     The seal is wanting.
                     </p>
                  </msItem>
